## 4. Moderation Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Report Received] --> B[Triage Assessment]
    B --> C{Severity Level}
    C -->|Low| D[Queue for Standard Review]
    C -->|Medium| E[Queue for Priority Review]
    C -->|High| F[Queue for Urgent Review]
    C -->|Critical| G[Immediate Action Required]
    
    D --> H[Assign Available Moderator]
    E --> I[Assign Senior Moderator]
    F --> J[Assign Safety Team Lead]
    G --> K[Emergency Protocol]
    
    H --> L[Moderator Investigation]
    I --> M[Senior Investigation]
    J --> N[Safety Investigation]
    K --> O[Immediate Content Removal]
    
    L --> P{Decision Required}
    M --> P
    N --> P
    O --> Q[Notify Safety Team]
    
    P -->|No Action| R[Dismiss Report]
    P -->|Warning| S[Issue Formal Warning]
    P -->|Content Action| T[Content Removal/Edit]
    P -->|Account Action| U[Account Suspension/Ban]
    
    R --> V[Update Trust Score]
    S --> V
    T --> V
    U --> V
    
    V --> W[Notify User]
    W --> X[Notify Reporter]
    X --> Y{User Appeals?}
    Y -->|No| Z[Close Case]
    Y -->|Yes| AA[Initiate Appeal Process]
    
    Q --> BB[Full Investigation]
    BB --> P
    AA --> CC[Assign Different Moderator]
    CC --> DD[Appeal Review]
    DD --> EE{Appeal Decision}
    EE -->|Uphold| Z
    EE -->|Reverse| FF[Reverse Action]
    FF --> V
```

