## 6. Escalation Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Issue Identified] --> B{Initial Assessment}
    B -->|Routine| C[Standard Process]
    B -->|Complex| D[Escalation Trigger]
    B -->|Urgent| E[Immediate Escalation]
    
    C --> F[Resolve at Current Level]
    D --> G[Escalation Criteria Check]
    E --> H[Emergency Escalation]
    
    G --> I{Escalation Level}
    I -->|Level 1| J[Senior Moderator]
    I -->|Level 2| K[Moderation Lead]
    I -->|Level 3| L[Community Manager]
    I -->|Level 4| M[Trust & Safety Team]
    
    H --> N[Assign Safety Team Lead]
    J --> O[Senior Review]
    K --> P[Lead Review]
    L --> Q[Manager Review]
    M --> R[Team Review]
    N --> S[Urgent Safety Review]
    
    O --> T{Resolution Possible?}
    P --> T
    Q --> T
    R --> T
    S --> U{Immediate Action Required?}
    
    T -->|Yes| V[Implement Solution]
    T -->|No| W[Further Escalation]
    U -->|Yes| X[Emergency Action]
    U -->|No| Y[Standard Safety Process]
    
    V --> Z[Document Resolution]
    W --> AA[Next Level Escalation]
    X --> BB[Document Emergency Action]
    Y --> CC[Standard Resolution]
    
    Z --> DD[Notify Stakeholders]
    AA --> I
    BB --> DD
    CC --> DD
    
    DD --> EE[Update Escalation Log]
    EE --> FF[Review Process Improvement]
```

