## 7. Appeal Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Receives Decision] --> B{Appeal Eligible?}
    B -->|No| C[Decision Final]
    B -->|Yes| D[Appeal Initiation]
    
    D --> E[Appeal Form Submission]
    E --> F[Appeal Validation]
    F --> G{Valid Appeal?}
    G -->|No| H[Reject Appeal]
    G -->|Yes| I[Assign Appeal Reviewer]
    
    I --> J{Original Reviewer Available?}
    J -->|Yes| K[Assign Different Reviewer]
    J -->|No| L[Assign Senior Reviewer]
    
    K --> M[Fresh Evidence Review]
    L --> M
    M --> N[Context Analysis]
    N --> O[Policy Re-evaluation]
    
    O --> P{Appeal Decision}
    P -->|Uphold Original| Q[Confirm Original Decision]
    P -->|Modify| R[Modify Original Decision]
    P -->|Reverse| S[Reverse Original Decision]
    
    Q --> T[Notify User of Upheld Decision]
    R --> U[Implement Modified Action]
    S --> V[Reverse Original Action]
    
    U --> W[Notify User of Modification]
    V --> X[Notify User of Reversal]
    T --> Y[Log Appeal Outcome]
    W --> Y
    X --> Y
    
    Y --> Z{Further Appeal Possible?}
    Z -->|No| AA[Appeal Process Complete]
    Z -->|Yes| BB[Final Appeal Level]
    
    BB --> CC[Executive Review]
    CC --> DD[Final Decision]
    DD --> EE[Implement Final Decision]
    EE --> AA
```

